Deployed LLMs are often invoked with prompt engineering or in-context learning in order to best shape the application inputs towards desired outputs.
 Notable LLMs that are widely used include
 the OpenAI family of GPT models, Google's PaLM
 models, Huawei's PanGu series, Meta's Llama family, and more. 
 LLM-based assistants such as Google Gemini or Bing Co-Pilot
 are gaining popularity.